The paper discusses quality control for crowdsourcing, which involves designing mechanisms to influence workers' behavior and developing statistical models to aggregate responses. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). However, given the focus on crowdsourcing and quality control, cs.HC and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.SI, and cs.IR.
